		<div class="comment_text"><p>Great, great demos.<br>Regarding step 4:</p><p>When I loaded this the first time, the pictures were red X's until they loaded.<br>Subsequent visits loaded instantly.<br>It reminds me of the @import CSS bug where the screen flashes before applying the CSS.<br>But the good news is that this means that Spry doesn't have to load everything before starting to display.</p><p>I would change<br>&lt;b style="cursor: pointer;"&gt;{name}&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;<br>to<br>&lt;a href="#"&gt;{name}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;</p><p>to simplify the example.<br>If people balk at using a href="#" because it would throw them to the top of the page, you could use<br>&lt;a href="#" onclick="aFunction();return false;"&gt;{name}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;<br>But that's muddying the example.</p><p>But I think making the names hyperlinks is a better practice than using the (deprecated) bold element with an inline style.<br>Wow!  I'm actually talking coherently about some of this stuff!</p><p>Here's how I reformatted step4:<br>&lt;style type="text/css"&gt;<br>h2 {<br>margin-top:0;<br>}<br>#bio{<br>float:right;<br>}<br>#List {<br>float:left;<br>}<br>&lt;/style&gt;<br>&lt;/head&gt;</p><p>&lt;body&gt;</p><p>&lt;div id="List" spry:region="mydata"&gt;<br>	Please click on one of the names below for more information:&lt;br&gt;<br>	&lt;div spry:repeat="mydata" onClick="mydata.setCurrentRow('{ds_RowID}');"&gt;<br>	&lt;a href="#" onclick="aFunction();return false;"&gt;{name}&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;<br>	&lt;/div&gt;<br>&lt;/div&gt;</p><p>&lt;div id="bio" spry:detailregion="mydata"&gt;<br>&lt;h2&gt;{name}&lt;/h2&gt;<br>{name} is {age} years old and is a {gender}<br>&lt;img src="{picture}" align="left"&gt;<br>&lt;/div&gt;</p></div>
